{
    "publish_date": "2013-05-03T15:07:28.000Z", 
    "score": 0.0003059578815268854, 
    "video_length": "PT6M30S", 
    "captions": [
        {
            "text": "So two guys walk into a bar.", 
            "dur": "1.456", 
            "start": "13.623"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Really?", 
            "dur": "0.629", 
            "start": "15.079"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "No, seriously.", 
            "dur": "1.086", 
            "start": "15.708"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Two guys walk into a bar,", 
            "dur": "1.57", 
            "start": "16.794"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "an ice cream bar:", 
            "dur": "1.396", 
            "start": "18.364"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Dave, a physicist working on the Large Hadron Collider at CERN,", 
            "dur": "3.937", 
            "start": "19.76"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the European laboratory for particle physics,", 
            "dur": "2.313", 
            "start": "23.697"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and Steve, a blues singer.", 
            "dur": "2.694", 
            "start": "26.01"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Dave, how&#39;s it going?&quot;", 
            "dur": "1.545", 
            "start": "28.704"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Steve, good to see you!&quot;", 
            "dur": "2.033", 
            "start": "30.249"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Two scoops of chocolate almond for me.&quot;", 
            "dur": "2.028", 
            "start": "32.282"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Vanilla shake.&quot;", 
            "dur": "1.212", 
            "start": "34.31"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Hey, I just saw something about the LHC on TV.", 
            "dur": "2.607", 
            "start": "35.522"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You guys found bozo in your detector?&quot;", 
            "dur": "2.604", 
            "start": "38.129"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Well, not exactly.", 
            "dur": "1.34", 
            "start": "40.733"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We found a boson,", 
            "dur": "1.327", 
            "start": "42.073"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "probably the Higgs boson.&quot;", 
            "dur": "1.844", 
            "start": "43.4"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;What&#39;s that?&quot;", 
            "dur": "1.001", 
            "start": "45.244"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;It&#39;s a particle.&quot;", 
            "dur": "1.235", 
            "start": "46.245"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Don&#39;t you find particles all the time?&quot;", 
            "dur": "2.139", 
            "start": "47.48"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Yes, but this one means", 
            "dur": "1.622", 
            "start": "49.619"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that the Higgs field might really exist.&quot;", 
            "dur": "2.522", 
            "start": "51.241"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Field? What field?&quot;", 
            "dur": "1.765", 
            "start": "53.763"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;The Higgs field.", 
            "dur": "1.472", 
            "start": "55.528"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s named after Peter Higgs,", 
            "dur": "1.793", 
            "start": "57"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "although many others contributed to the idea.", 
            "dur": "2.377", 
            "start": "58.793"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It isn&#39;t a field, like where you grow corn,", 
            "dur": "2.751", 
            "start": "61.17"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but a hypothetical, invisible kind of force field", 
            "dur": "3.381", 
            "start": "63.921"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that pervades the whole universe.&quot;", 
            "dur": "1.918", 
            "start": "67.302"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Hmmmm, okay.", 
            "dur": "2.351", 
            "start": "69.22"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If it pervades the whole universe,", 
            "dur": "1.862", 
            "start": "71.571"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "how come I&#39;ve never seen it?", 
            "dur": "1.632", 
            "start": "73.433"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That&#39;s a bit strange.&quot;", 
            "dur": "2.293", 
            "start": "75.065"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Well, actually, it&#39;s not that strange.", 
            "dur": "2.085", 
            "start": "77.358"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Think of the air around us.", 
            "dur": "1.834", 
            "start": "79.443"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We can&#39;t see it or smell it.", 
            "dur": "1.956", 
            "start": "81.277"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Well, perhaps in some places we can.", 
            "dur": "2.086", 
            "start": "83.233"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But we can detect its presence with sophisticated equipment,", 
            "dur": "4.262", 
            "start": "85.319"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "like our own bodies.", 
            "dur": "2.167", 
            "start": "89.581"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So the fact that we can&#39;t see something", 
            "dur": "2.622", 
            "start": "91.748"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "just makes it a bit harder to determine", 
            "dur": "1.966", 
            "start": "94.37"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "whether its really there or not.&quot;", 
            "dur": "1.938", 
            "start": "96.336"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Alright, go on.&quot;", 
            "dur": "2.143", 
            "start": "98.274"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;So, we believe this Higgs field is all around us,", 
            "dur": "3.378", 
            "start": "100.417"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "everywhere in the universe.", 
            "dur": "1.545", 
            "start": "103.795"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And what it does is rather special -", 
            "dur": "2.466", 
            "start": "105.34"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "it gives mass to elementary particles.&quot;", 
            "dur": "2.83", 
            "start": "107.806"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;What&#39;s an elementary particle?&quot;", 
            "dur": "1.918", 
            "start": "110.636"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;An elementary particle is what we call", 
            "dur": "2.136", 
            "start": "112.554"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "particles that have no structure,", 
            "dur": "2.378", 
            "start": "114.69"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "they can&#39;t be divided,", 
            "dur": "1.827", 
            "start": "117.068"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "they&#39;re the basic building blocks of the universe.&quot;", 
            "dur": "2.758", 
            "start": "118.895"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;I thought those were atoms.&quot;", 
            "dur": "1.546", 
            "start": "121.653"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Well, atoms are actually made of smaller components,", 
            "dur": "3.836", 
            "start": "123.199"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "protons, neutrons, and electrons.", 
            "dur": "2.412", 
            "start": "127.035"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "While electrons are fundamental particles,", 
            "dur": "3.003", 
            "start": "129.447"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "neutrons and protons are not.", 
            "dur": "2.377", 
            "start": "132.45"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "They are made up of other fundamental particles called quarks.&quot;", 
            "dur": "3.712", 
            "start": "134.827"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Sounds like Russian dolls.", 
            "dur": "1.46", 
            "start": "138.539"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Does it ever end?&quot;", 
            "dur": "1.624", 
            "start": "139.999"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Actually, we don&#39;t really know.", 
            "dur": "1.921", 
            "start": "141.623"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But our current understanding", 
            "dur": "1.627", 
            "start": "143.544"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is called the Standard Model.", 
            "dur": "2.711", 
            "start": "145.171"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In it, there are two types of fundamental particles:", 
            "dur": "3.063", 
            "start": "147.882"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the fermions, that make up matter,", 
            "dur": "2.609", 
            "start": "150.945"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and the bosons, that carry forces.", 
            "dur": "3.177", 
            "start": "153.554"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We often order these particles", 
            "dur": "2.211", 
            "start": "156.731"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "according to their properties, such as mass.", 
            "dur": "3.037", 
            "start": "158.942"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We can measure the masses of the particles,", 
            "dur": "2.481", 
            "start": "161.979"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but we never really knew where this mass came from", 
            "dur": "3.748", 
            "start": "164.46"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "or why they have the masses they do.&quot;", 
            "dur": "2.742", 
            "start": "168.208"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;So how does this Higgs field thing explain mass?&quot;", 
            "dur": "3.333", 
            "start": "170.95"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Well, when a particle passes through the Higgs field,", 
            "dur": "3.17", 
            "start": "174.283"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "it interacts and gets mass.", 
            "dur": "2.92", 
            "start": "177.453"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The more it interacts, the more mass it has.&quot;", 
            "dur": "2.968", 
            "start": "180.373"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;OK, I kind of get that, but is it really that important?", 
            "dur": "2.454", 
            "start": "183.341"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I mean, what if there were no Higgs field?&quot;", 
            "dur": "2.002", 
            "start": "185.795"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;If there were no Higgs field,", 
            "dur": "1.46", 
            "start": "187.797"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the world wouldn&#39;t exist at all.", 
            "dur": "2.21", 
            "start": "189.257"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "There would be no stars, no planets, no air, no anything,", 
            "dur": "3.17", 
            "start": "191.467"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "not even that spoon or the ice cream you&#39;re eating.&quot;", 
            "dur": "3.086", 
            "start": "194.637"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Oh, that would be bad.", 
            "dur": "1.085", 
            "start": "197.723"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Okay, but where does this Higgs boson fit into things?&quot;", 
            "dur": "3.629", 
            "start": "198.808"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Alright, now, you see the cherry in my shake?&quot;", 
            "dur": "2.243", 
            "start": "202.437"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Can I have it?&quot;", 
            "dur": "1.049", 
            "start": "204.68"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;No, not yet. We have to use it as an analogy first.&quot;", 
            "dur": "3.72", 
            "start": "205.729"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Oh, right, the cherry&#39;s the Higgs boson.&quot;", 
            "dur": "2.462", 
            "start": "209.449"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;No, not quite.", 
            "dur": "1.87", 
            "start": "211.911"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The cherry is a particle moving through the Higgs field, the shake.", 
            "dur": "4.804", 
            "start": "213.781"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The shake gives the cherry its mass.&quot;", 
            "dur": "2.75", 
            "start": "218.585"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;I get it. Okay, so the molecules of the shake are the Higgs bosons!&quot;", 
            "dur": "4.493", 
            "start": "221.335"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Well, you&#39;re getting closer.", 
            "dur": "1.91", 
            "start": "225.828"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It takes an excitation of the Higgs field", 
            "dur": "2.979", 
            "start": "227.738"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to produce the Higgs boson.", 
            "dur": "2.466", 
            "start": "230.717"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So, for example, if I were to add energy", 
            "dur": "2.416", 
            "start": "233.183"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "by, say, dropping this cherry in the shake,&quot;", 
            "dur": "2.798", 
            "start": "235.599"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Ah, then the drops that spill on the bar", 
            "dur": "1.423", 
            "start": "238.397"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "are the Higgs bosons.&quot;", 
            "dur": "1.788", 
            "start": "239.82"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Almost! The splash itself is the Higgs boson.&quot;", 
            "dur": "5.509", 
            "start": "241.608"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Are you serious?&quot;", 
            "dur": "2.441", 
            "start": "247.117"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Well, that&#39;s what quantum mechanics teaches us.", 
            "dur": "3.219", 
            "start": "249.558"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In fact, all particles are excitations of fields.&quot;", 
            "dur": "5.022", 
            "start": "252.777"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Okay, right. Well, I kind of see why you like particle physics,", 
            "dur": "3.529", 
            "start": "257.799"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "it&#39;s quite cool,", 
            "dur": "1.707", 
            "start": "261.328"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "strange, but cool.&quot;", 
            "dur": "2.297", 
            "start": "263.035"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Yeah, you could call it a bit strange,", 
            "dur": "2.098", 
            "start": "265.332"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "it&#39;s not like everyday life.", 
            "dur": "2.281", 
            "start": "267.43"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The Higgs boson is an excitation of the Higgs field.", 
            "dur": "5.172", 
            "start": "269.711"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "By finding the Higgs boson,", 
            "dur": "2.002", 
            "start": "274.883"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we know that the Higgs field exists.&quot;", 
            "dur": "3.349", 
            "start": "276.885"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Right. So now you found it,", 
            "dur": "1.745", 
            "start": "280.234"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we know this Higgs field exists.", 
            "dur": "2.038", 
            "start": "281.979"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You must be done.", 
            "dur": "1.168", 
            "start": "284.017"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Is there anything left of particle physics?&quot;", 
            "dur": "2.627", 
            "start": "285.185"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Actually, we&#39;ve just begun.", 
            "dur": "2.841", 
            "start": "287.812"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s a bit like, you know, when Columbus thought", 
            "dur": "2.966", 
            "start": "290.653"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "he had found a new route to India.", 
            "dur": "2.78", 
            "start": "293.619"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "He&#39;d, indeed, found something new,", 
            "dur": "2.8", 
            "start": "296.399"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but not quite what he was expecting.", 
            "dur": "2.336", 
            "start": "299.199"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So, first, we need to make sure that the boson we found", 
            "dur": "3.878", 
            "start": "301.535"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is actually the Higgs boson.", 
            "dur": "2.837", 
            "start": "305.413"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It seems to fit, but we need to measure", 
            "dur": "2.052", 
            "start": "308.25"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "its properties to be sure.&quot;", 
            "dur": "2.16", 
            "start": "310.302"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;How&#39;d you do that?&quot;", 
            "dur": "0.937", 
            "start": "312.462"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Take a lot more data.", 
            "dur": "1.997", 
            "start": "313.399"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This new boson lives for only a very short time", 
            "dur": "3.489", 
            "start": "315.396"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "before it breaks down or decays", 
            "dur": "1.628", 
            "start": "318.885"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "into lighter, more stable particles.", 
            "dur": "2.865", 
            "start": "320.513"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "By measuring these particles,", 
            "dur": "1.395", 
            "start": "323.378"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "you learn about the properties of the boson.&quot;", 
            "dur": "2.878", 
            "start": "324.773"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;And what exactly are you looking for?&quot;", 
            "dur": "2.165", 
            "start": "327.651"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Well, the Standard Model predicts how often", 
            "dur": "3.099", 
            "start": "329.816"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and in what ways the Higgs boson would decay", 
            "dur": "2.525", 
            "start": "332.915"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to the various, lighter particles.", 
            "dur": "2.56", 
            "start": "335.44"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So we want to see if the particle we have found", 
            "dur": "2.711", 
            "start": "338"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is the one predicted by the Standard Model", 
            "dur": "2.783", 
            "start": "340.711"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "or if it fits into other possible theoretical models.&quot;", 
            "dur": "3.424", 
            "start": "343.494"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;And if it fits a different model?&quot;", 
            "dur": "2.006", 
            "start": "346.918"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;That would be even more exciting!", 
            "dur": "2.624", 
            "start": "348.924"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In fact, that&#39;s how science advances.", 
            "dur": "3.086", 
            "start": "351.548"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We replace old models with new ones", 
            "dur": "2.836", 
            "start": "354.634"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "if they better explain our observations.&quot;", 
            "dur": "2.721", 
            "start": "357.47"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Right, so it seems like finding this Higgs boson", 
            "dur": "3.119", 
            "start": "360.191"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "gives a direction for exploration,", 
            "dur": "2.252", 
            "start": "363.31"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "a bit like that Columbus guy heading west.&quot;", 
            "dur": "2.627", 
            "start": "365.562"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Exactly! And this is really just the beginning.&quot;", 
            "dur": "3.704", 
            "start": "368.189"
        }
    ], 
